cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.PL, cs.CE 

This paper focuses on the human aspects of software development and the need to incorporate affect measurements to enhance management styles. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the linkage between affects and cognitive processing activities, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also involves programming tasks, which could be related to programming languages (cs.PL) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
